<paragraph base="SL32729" principles="yes" id="IAS38_100"><paranum>100</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 38"/><data name="paranum" value="100"/></prolog><body><p outputclass="keep_with_next" id="IAS38_P0284">The <xref base="SL141719" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0074">residual value<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0335"/></ph></xref> of an <xref base="SL141716" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0070">intangible asset<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0193"/></ph></xref> with a finite <xref base="SL141720" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0075">useful life<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0380"/></ph></xref> shall be assumed to be zero unless: </p><ol base="SL141940" type="lower-alpha" id="IAS38_L0033"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p base="SL141942" id="IAS38_P0285">there is a commitment by a third party to purchase the asset at the end of its useful life; or</p>                </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p base="SL141944" id="IAS38_P0287">there is an <xref base="SL141693" href="../ifrs13/IFRS13_APPA.dita#IFRS13_APPA/IFRS13_DI0001" scope="local">active market<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0007"/></ph></xref> (as defined in IFRS 13) for the asset and:</p>         <ol base="SL141945" type="lower-roman" id="IAS38_L0034"><li><li_value>(i)</li_value>             <p base="SL141947" id="IAS38_P0288">residual value can be determined by reference to that market; and</p>           </li><li><li_value>(ii)</li_value>             <p base="SL141949" id="IAS38_P0289">it is probable that such a market will exist at the end of the asset&#x2019;s useful life.</p>           </li></ol>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>